        <!-- Security Assessment -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Security Concerns</h2>
            
            <h3>1. Email Infrastructure Exposure</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Multiple email-related subdomains are publicly accessible</li>
                <li>Webmail interfaces present attack vectors for credential harvesting</li>
                <li>Potential for email-based social engineering attacks</li>
                <li>Risk of unauthorized email access and data exfiltration</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>2. Control Panel Services</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>cPanel-related subdomains suggest administrative interface exposure</li>
                <li>Risk of credential brute-force attacks on admin panels</li>
                <li>Potential for complete server compromise if accessed</li>
                <li>Calendar and contact services may contain sensitive business data</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>3. File Storage Access</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>webdisk subdomain indicates potential file storage access</li>
                <li>Risk of unauthorized file access and data breaches</li>
                <li>Potential for malware upload and distribution</li>
                <li>Business-critical documents may be exposed</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>4. Autodiscover Service</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Email configuration information potentially exposed</li>
                <li>Risk of information disclosure for email infrastructure</li>
                <li>Could aid attackers in email-based attacks</li>
                <li>May reveal internal network information</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
